      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW MONET (7) charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, giving a huge sight but headed late when a 4 length second (30.20) over 525m at this track. Sure to be about the mark. SOCIALISM (1) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 6th and beaten 10 lengths at Geelong (26.84). Got the money at her only try from this box. Key player if finds best. FEAR THE BEER (3) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (30.21) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from five starts. Expected to feature in the finish. HE SHINES (2) can measure up with the right run.",
